+      </header>
+
+      <main class="content">
+        <section class="hero">
+          <h1>Export your Kindle highlights.</h1>
+          <p>
+            One bookmarklet click on Kindle Notebook downloads every highlight and note you
+            have into tidy markdown files, one book per file, ready for local tools and plain
+            text workflows.
+          </p>
+        </section>
+
+        <section class="install-panel">
+          <p class="install-label">Step 1 — Drag this into your bookmarks bar</p>
+          <a class="bookmarklet" href="javascript:(function()%7Bfunction%20runClippingsBookmarklet()%20%7B%0A%20%20window.alert(%22Clippings%20bookmarklet%20placeholder%22)%3B%0A%7D%3BrunClippingsBookmarklet()%3B%7D)()" draggable="true">Export Kindle Highlights</a>
+          <p class="install-help">Keep the button in your browser bookmarks bar so you can run the export from Kindle Notebook.</p>
+        </section>
+
+        <section class="steps">
+          <ol start="2">
+            <li>
+              <strong>Open Kindle Notebook</strong>
+              <span>Visit <a href="https://read.amazon.com/notebook" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">read.amazon.com/notebook</a> while logged in to Amazon.</span>
+            </li>
+            <li>
+              <strong>Click the bookmarklet</strong>
+              <span>Use <em>Export Kindle Highlights</em> from your bookmarks bar to start the scrape and export flow.</span>
+            </li>
+            <li>
+              <strong>Download your zip</strong>
+              <span>A zip file downloads automatically with one markdown file per book.</span>
+            </li>
+          </ol>
+        </section>
+
+        <section class="sample">
+          <p class="sample-label">Sample markdown output</p>
+          <pre><code># The Pragmatic Programmer
+author: David Thomas, Andrew Hunt
+asin: B07VRS84D1
+last_annotated: 2024-11-03
+highlights: 24
+notes: 6
+
+---
+
+location: 312 | page: 28 | added: 2024-10-15
+&lt;highlight&gt;
+Care about your craft.
+&lt;/highlight&gt;
+&lt;note&gt;
+Core thesis. Revisit when motivation dips.
+&lt;/note&gt;</code></pre>
+        </section>
+      </main>
+    </div>
   </body>
 </html>

